Scanning


The ports are filtered on the target machine. I used the command sudo nmap -sS -v -v -Pn 192.168.170.148 -g 80 -p- to scan ports by manipulating my source port as HTTP.


From the aggressive nmap scan above, there are interesting applications running on the target machine. I will begin enumeration with SMB first. The FTP application also allows anonymous login!
